<hom role=""n""><pos>n</pos>
<sense n=""0""><trans> fresh fish. </trans>
<eg><i lang=""ceb"">Musúruy siyag lab-as káda buntag,</i><trans> She peddles fresh fish every morning. </trans></eg>
</sense></hom>
<hom role=""v""><pos>v</pos>
<sense n=""1""><number>1</number> <itype>[B2]</itype><trans> be fresh. </trans>
</sense>
<sense n=""2""><number>2</number> <itype>[AB2; a12]</itype><trans> make s.t. fresh to one’s mind. </trans>
<eg><i lang=""ceb"">Mga handumánan nga naglab-as sa átung kagahápun,</i><trans> Memories that keep our past fresh. </trans></eg>
</sense></hom>
<entry><form id=""nilab-as"" lang=""ceb"">nilab-as</form>
<hom role=""a""><pos>a</pos>
<sense n=""0""><trans> in a fresh way. </trans>
</sense></hom>
<hom role=""v""><pos>v</pos>
<sense n=""0""> <itype>[a1]</itype><trans> do s.t. in a fresh way. </trans>
<eg><i lang=""ceb"">Ginilab-as ku níyag pangutána,</i><trans> He asked me in a disrespectful way. </trans></eg>
</sense></hom></entry>
<entry><form id=""lab-asixra"" lang=""ceb""><abbr expan=""lab-asíra"">-íra</abbr></form>
<hom role=""n""><pos>n</pos>
<sense n=""0""><trans> female fish vendor. </trans>
