<hom role=""v""><pos>v</pos>
<sense n=""1""><number>1</number> <itype>[B2; c1]</itype><trans> for s.t. that wraps s.t. to come open. </trans>
<eg><i lang=""ceb"">Miliskag ang dáhun sa ságing nga gipustan sa bulad,</i><trans> The banana leaves which the dried fish were wrapped in came undone. </trans></eg>
<eg><i lang=""ceb"">Nagkaliskag ang sáku kay labihang dasúka,</i><trans> The sack is coming apart because it was filled too full. </trans></eg>
<eg><i lang=""ceb"">Liskága (iliskag) ang baat,</i><trans> Untie the string. </trans></eg>
</sense>
<sense n=""1a""><number>1a</number><trans> for s.t. woven to get undone. </trans>
<eg><i lang=""ceb"">Naliskag ang banig kay wà masapay,</i><trans> The mat came undone because the edges weren’t closed up. </trans></eg>
</sense>
<sense n=""2""><number>2</number> <itype>[B2N]</itype><trans> <tr>spread out</tr>, <tr>stick out</tr>. </trans>
<eg><i lang=""ceb"">Maliskag ang balhíbu sa pábung duúlun,</i><trans> The turkey puffs up its feathers if you get near it. </trans></eg>
<eg><i lang=""ceb"">Naliskag ang íyang dunggan pagkadungug sa íyang ngā́n,</i><trans> Her ears perked up when she heard her name. </trans></eg>
</sense></hom>
<hom role=""a""><pos>a</pos>
<sense n=""0""><trans> <tr>spread out</tr>, <tr>undone</tr>. </trans>
<eg><i lang=""ceb"">Liskag ug tiil,</i><trans> Spreading feet.
